#. <section class="sutta" id="sn46.30"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn46.30:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 46"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 46"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn46.30:0.2"
msgid "3. Udāyivagga"
msgstr "3. With Udāyī"

#. </p><h1>
#. VAR: 30. Udāyisutta → udāyīsuttaṃ (bj) | udāyi (pts1)
msgctxt "sn46.30:0.3"
msgid "30. Udāyisutta"
msgstr "30. With Udāyī"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.30:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sumbhesu viharati setakaṃ nāma sumbhānaṃ nigamo."
msgstr ""
"At one time the Buddha was staying in the land of the Sumbhas, near the town "
"of the Sumbhas called Sedaka."

msgctxt "sn46.30:1.2"
msgid ""
"Atha kho āyasmā udāyī yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami … pe … ekamantaṃ nisinno "
"kho āyasmā udāyī bhagavantaṃ etadavoca:"
msgstr "Then Venerable Udāyī went up to the Buddha … and said to him:"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.30:2.1"
msgid "“Acchariyaṃ, bhante, abbhutaṃ, bhante."
msgstr "“It’s incredible, sir, it’s amazing!"

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.2"
msgid ""
"Yāva bahukatañca me, bhante, bhagavati pemañca gāravo ca hirī ca ottappañca."
msgstr ""
"How helpful my love and respect for the Buddha have been, and my sense of "
"conscience and prudence."

# I’m not sure why BB finds this sense problematic.
#. VAR: dhammena → dhamme (?)
msgctxt "sn46.30:2.3"
msgid ""
"Ahañhi, bhante, pubbe agārikabhūto samāno abahukato ahosiṃ dhammena "
"abahukato saṃghena."
msgstr ""
"For when I was still a layman, I wasn’t helped much by the teaching or the "
"Saṅgha."

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.4"
msgid ""
"So khvāhaṃ bhagavati pemañca gāravañca hiriñca ottappañca sampassamāno "
"agārasmā anagāriyaṃ pabbajito."
msgstr ""
"But when I considered my love and respect for the Buddha, and my sense of "
"conscience and prudence, I went forth from the lay life to homelessness."

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.5"
msgid "Tassa me bhagavā dhammaṃ desesi:"
msgstr "The Buddha taught me the Dhamma:"

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.6"
msgid "‘iti rūpaṃ, iti rūpassa samudayo, iti rūpassa atthaṅgamo;"
msgstr "‘Such is form, such is the origin of form, such is the ending of form."

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.7"
msgid "iti vedanā … pe …"
msgstr "Such is feeling …"

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.8"
msgid "iti saññā …"
msgstr "Such is perception …"

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.9"
msgid "iti saṅkhārā …"
msgstr "Such are choices …"

msgctxt "sn46.30:2.10"
msgid "iti viññāṇaṃ, iti viññāṇassa samudayo, iti viññāṇassa atthaṅgamo’ti."
msgstr ""
"Such is consciousness, such is the origin of consciousness, such is the "
"ending of consciousness.’"

# BB has “surge and decline’. The term means” upright and upturned", i.e. tumbling, churning.
#. </p><p>
#. <a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pli5.90"></a>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc3"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.30:3.1"
msgid ""
"So khvāhaṃ, bhante, suññāgāragato imesaṃ pañcupādānakkhandhānaṃ "
"ukkujjāvakujjaṃ samparivattento ‘idaṃ dukkhan’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘"
"ayaṃ dukkhasamudayo’ti yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodho’ti "
"yathābhūtaṃ abbhaññāsiṃ, ‘ayaṃ dukkhanirodhagāminī paṭipadā’ti yathābhūtaṃ "
"abbhaññāsiṃ."
msgstr ""
"Then, while staying in an empty hut, I followed the churning of the five "
"grasping aggregates. I truly understood: ‘This is suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"origin of suffering’ … ‘This is the cessation of suffering’ … ‘This is the "
"practice that leads to the cessation of suffering’."

msgctxt "sn46.30:3.2"
msgid "Dhammo ca me, bhante, abhisamito, maggo ca me paṭiladdho;"
msgstr "I comprehended the teaching; I acquired the path."

# tatha tatha viharati: a similar idiom is found in an6.14, an6.15
msgctxt "sn46.30:3.3"
msgid ""
"yo me bhāvito bahulīkato tathā tathā viharantaṃ tathattāya upanessati "
"yathāhaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When developed and cultivated as I’m living in such a way, it will bring me "
"to such a state that I will understand:"

msgctxt "sn46.30:3.4"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānissāmi."
msgstr ""
"‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be "
"done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc4"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.30:4.1"
msgid ""
"Satisambojjhaṅgo me, bhante, paṭiladdho, yo me bhāvito bahulīkato tathā "
"tathā viharantaṃ tathattāya upanessati yathāhaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"I acquired the awakening factors of mindfulness, investigation of "
"principles, energy, rapture, tranquility, immersion, and equanimity."

msgctxt "sn46.30:4.2"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānissāmi … pe …"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "sn46.30:4.3"
msgid ""
"upekkhāsambojjhaṅgo me, bhante, paṭiladdho, yo me bhāvito bahulīkato tathā "
"tathā viharantaṃ tathattāya upanessati yathāhaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"When developed and cultivated as I’m living in such a way, they will bring "
"me to such a state that I will understand:"

msgctxt "sn46.30:4.4"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānissāmi."
msgstr ""
"‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be "
"done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’"

msgctxt "sn46.30:4.5"
msgid ""
"Ayaṃ kho me, bhante, maggo paṭiladdho, yo me bhāvito bahulīkato tathā tathā "
"viharantaṃ tathattāya upanessati yathāhaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"This is the path that I acquired. When developed and cultivated as I’m "
"living in such a way, it will bring me to such a state that I will "
"understand:"

msgctxt "sn46.30:4.6"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānissāmī”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be "
"done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc5"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.30:5.1"
msgid "“Sādhu sādhu, udāyi."
msgstr "“Good, good, Udāyī!"

msgctxt "sn46.30:5.2"
msgid ""
"Eso hi te, udāyi, maggo paṭiladdho, yo te bhāvito bahulīkato tathā tathā "
"viharantaṃ tathattāya upanessati yathā tvaṃ:"
msgstr ""
"For that is indeed the path that you acquired. When developed and cultivated "
"as you’re living in such a way, it will bring you to such a state that you "
"will understand:"

msgctxt "sn46.30:5.3"
msgid ""
"‘khīṇā jāti, vusitaṃ brahmacariyaṃ, kataṃ karaṇīyaṃ, nāparaṃ itthattāyā’ti "
"pajānissasī”ti."
msgstr ""
"‘Rebirth is ended, the spiritual journey has been completed, what had to be "
"done has been done, there is no return to any state of existence.’”"

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.30:5.4"
msgid "Dasamaṃ."
msgstr ""

#. </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "sn46.30:5.5"
msgid "Udāyivaggo tatiyo."
msgstr ""

#. </p><blockquote class="uddanagatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc6"></a>
msgctxt "sn46.30:6.1"
msgid "Bodhāya desanā ṭhānā,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn46.30:6.2"
msgid "ayoniso cāparihānī;"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn46.30:6.3"
msgid "Khayo nirodho nibbedho,"
msgstr ""

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn46.30:6.4"
msgid "ekadhammo udāyināti."
msgstr ""
